{"author":{"id":"68dfa65ee618df2786e7da658bbfbbcc1f0c757170d9426e314e5f0886bcc55d"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1633426058,"nonce":"WWSSziJIDvs0VybCviqT0FmQjQY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s48kF5B","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4008","origin":"github"},"title":"Guidelines for additional output parameters","message":"In a recent (short) discussion (https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/pull/4006#discussion_r721666177) we were wondering what's the best way to choose which outputs a tool should produce:\n\n- multiple booleans \n- one select \n\nWondering if we should try to standardize this in the IUC guidelines?\n\nFor me a select is favorable for the following reasons:\n\n- its more compact (except for one output)\n- one can contrain them, e.g. requiering at least one (`min=\"1\"`) or requiring exactly one (`type=\"radio\"`)\n\nHere is how the two options look: \n\n![bool](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25689525/135995952-b7e25fa7-3d30-4f9c-a4dd-4f2c9a2d30da.png)\n![select](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25689525/135995978-2308b735-ff06-40ce-ada4-1380a4c95d13.png)\n\nMaybe add thumbs up/down reactions to the issue if you support/not support standardization... or add comments with arguments.","files":null}]}